  <data name="String16" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Support the following methods and use them in multiple ways ';' Separate
1. Field: Directly output the field data, for example: fmem; Addtime, etc
2. @SQL{}: Output the SQL query results, automatically match the result set format when outputting JSON, support @p1@ and [col] syntax
3. @code: Code interface, for example, @code (SQL. vvv. ddd, 1|[fid]|@p1@), where [name] represents a value in the dataset with a column name of name
4. @api_: Api interface, such as @api_/yanshi/dic/?GetList/[p1]/[p2]
5. @para: Site parameters
6. @KeyValue{col, 1, SQL}: Based on the SQL statement of keyValue, escape the column. The second parameter 0 is all escaped, 1 only exports the escape, and 2 only escapes the list
7. ! Beginning: For example !abc(null|x1)(|x2)(val0|x3)(other|x4) represents the content displayed when the values of column abc are non-existent, empty, val0, or other, respectively</value>
